data.title: Colorado Parks & Wildlife
data.meta_description: Colorado Parks and Wildlife is a nationally recognized leader in conservation, outdoor recreation and wildlife management. The agency​ manages 42 state parks, all of Colorado's wildlife, more than 300 state wildlife areas and a host of recreational programs. CPW issues hunting and fishing licenses, conducts research to improve wildlife management activities, protects high priority wildlife habitat through acquisitions and partnerships, provides technical assistance to private and other public landowners concerning wildlife and habitat management and develops programs to understand, protect and recover threatened and endangered species.
data.text:
Events

Introduction to Archery @ Barr Lake State Park

Whether you’re new or a pro to the sport, archery at Barr Lake is a great time to test your skills and have fun. Learn about safety, proper techniques and then have a try at our archery range

Full Moon Hike @ Barr Lake State Park (Sturgeon Moon)

Explore Barr Lake at Dusk! Envision yourself taking a short evening walk with a Park Naturalist. Moon walk programs are designed for adults and families with children age 6 and up.

Yoga at Barr Lake State Park

These classes are for beginners and experienced Yogis. Bring a mat or a large towel and a water bottle. There are a limited number of mats available to borrow that day.

Yoga at the Gazebo @ Barr Lake State Park

Meet at the bridge by the Nature Center and be taken by golf carts to the gazebo to enjoy yoga time in the fresh air.

Toddler Story Time at Barr Lake State Park

Bring your preschooler to the Nature Center and listen to stories about the natural world while learning about plants, animals and our planet.
